article.description: — Ricky Council IV registered 11 points as Wichita State defeated Tulsa 58-48 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Council IV scores 11 to lift Wichita St. over Tulsa 58-48
article.linkText: Council IV scores 11 to lift Wichita St. over Tulsa 58-48
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- — Ricky Council IV registered 11 points as Wichita State defeated Tulsa 58-48 on Tuesday night. Tyson Etienne had 10 points for Wichita State (11-8, 2-5 American Athletic Conference). Morris Udeze added eight rebounds and four blocks. Dexter Dennis had six rebounds. Tulsa totaled 18 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Sam Griffin had 17 points for the Golden Hurricane (7-13, 1-8). Rey Idowu added eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
